11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Education
14 4–148.
15 (A) EACH COUNTY BOARD LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL:
16 (1) DESIGNATE A LOCAL POINT OF CONTACT FOR ALL
17 CYBERSECURITY–RELATED COMMUNICATIONS; AND
18 (2) NOTIFY THE STATE CHIEF INFORMATION SECURITY OFFICER OF:
19 (I) THE DESIGNATION; AND
20 (II) ANY SUBSEQUENT UPDATE TO THE DESIGNATION.
21 (B) (1) BEGINNING IN 2027, EACH LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL:
22 (I) COMPLY WITH THE STATE MINIMUM CYBERSECURITY
23 STANDARDS ESTABLISHED BY THE DEPARTMENT OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY;
24 AND
25 (II) CONDUCT A CYBERSECURITY MATURITY ASSESSMENT
26 EVERY 2 YEARS.
27 (2) ON OR BEFORE JUNE 30, 2027, AND EACH JUNE 30 EVERY 2
28 YEARS THEREAFTER, EACH LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL CERTIFY TO THE OFFICE
29 OF SECURITY MANAGEMENT WITHIN THE DEPARTMENT OF INFORMATION
30 TECHNOLOGY COMPLIANCE WITH THE STATE MINIMUM CYBERSECURITY
31 STANDARDS ESTABLISHED BY THE DEPARTMENT OF INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY.

